trans-unit.source: This article shows how to move your telemetry data from [Visual Studio Application Insights][start] into an Azure SQL database by using [Continuous Export][export] and a small amount of code.
trans-unit.target: This article shows how to move your telemetry data from [Visual Studio Application Insights][start] into an Azure SQL database by using [Continuous Export][export] and a small amount of code.

trans-unit.source: Continuous export moves your telemetry into Azure Storage in JSON format, so we'll write some code to parse the JSON objects and create rows in a database table.
trans-unit.target: Continuous export moves your telemetry into Azure Storage in JSON format, so we'll write some code to parse the JSON objects and create rows in a database table.

trans-unit.source: (More generally, Continuous Export is the way to do your own analysis of the telemetry your apps send to Application Insights.
trans-unit.target: (More generally, Continuous Export is the way to do your own analysis of the telemetry your apps send to Application Insights.

trans-unit.source: You could adapt this code sample to do other things with the exported telemetry.)
trans-unit.target: You could adapt this code sample to do other things with the exported telemetry.)

trans-unit.source: We'll start with the assumption that you already have the app you want to monitor.
trans-unit.target: We'll start with the assumption that you already have the app you want to monitor.

trans-unit.source: Add Application Insights SDK
trans-unit.target: Add Application Insights SDK

trans-unit.source: To monitor your application, you [add an Application Insights SDK][start] to your application.
trans-unit.target: To monitor your application, you [add an Application Insights SDK][start] to your application.

trans-unit.source: There are different SDKs and helper tools for different platforms, IDEs and languages.
trans-unit.target: There are different SDKs and helper tools for different platforms, IDEs and languages.

trans-unit.source: You can monitor web pages, Java or ASP.NET web servers, and mobile devices of several kinds.
trans-unit.target: You can monitor web pages, Java or ASP.NET web servers, and mobile devices of several kinds.

trans-unit.source: All the SDKs send telemetry to the [Application Insights portal][portal], where you can use our powerful analysis and diagnostic tools, and export the data to storage.
trans-unit.target: All the SDKs send telemetry to the [Application Insights portal][portal], where you can use our powerful analysis and diagnostic tools, and export the data to storage.

trans-unit.source: To get started:
trans-unit.target: To get started:

trans-unit.source: Get an [account in Microsoft Azure](http://azure.microsoft.com/pricing/).
trans-unit.target: Get an [account in Microsoft Azure](http://azure.microsoft.com/pricing/).

trans-unit.source: In the [Azure portal][portal], add a new Application Insights resource for your app:
trans-unit.target: In the [Azure portal][portal], add a new Application Insights resource for your app:

trans-unit.source: Choose New, Developer Services, Application Insights, and choose the type of application
trans-unit.target: Choose New, Developer Services, Application Insights, and choose the type of application

trans-unit.source: Open Quick Start to find how to set up the SDK for your app type.
trans-unit.target: Open Quick Start to find how to set up the SDK for your app type.

trans-unit.source: Choose Quick Start and follow instructions
trans-unit.target: Choose Quick Start and follow instructions

trans-unit.source: If your app type isn't listed, take a look at the [Getting Started][start] page.
trans-unit.target: If your app type isn't listed, take a look at the [Getting Started][start] page.

trans-unit.source: In this example, we're monitoring a web app, so we can use the Azure tools in Visual Studio to install the SDK.
trans-unit.target: In this example, we're monitoring a web app, so we can use the Azure tools in Visual Studio to install the SDK.

trans-unit.source: We tell it the name of our Application Insights resource:
trans-unit.target: We tell it the name of our Application Insights resource:

trans-unit.source: In Visual Studio, in the New Project dialog, check Add Application Insights, and under Send telemetry to, choose to create a new app, or use an existing one.
trans-unit.target: In Visual Studio, in the New Project dialog, check Add Application Insights, and under Send telemetry to, choose to create a new app, or use an existing one.

trans-unit.source: Create storage in Azure
trans-unit.target: Create storage in Azure

trans-unit.source: Create a storage account in your subscription in the [Azure portal][portal].
trans-unit.target: Create a storage account in your subscription in the [Azure portal][portal].

trans-unit.source: In Azure portal, choose New, Data, Storage
trans-unit.target: In Azure portal, choose New, Data, Storage

trans-unit.source: Create a container
trans-unit.target: Create a container

trans-unit.source: In the new storage, select Containers and then Add
trans-unit.target: In the new storage, select Containers and then Add

trans-unit.source: Start continuous export to Azure storage
trans-unit.target: Start continuous export to Azure storage

trans-unit.source: In the Azure portal, browse to the Application Insights resource you created for your application.
trans-unit.target: In the Azure portal, browse to the Application Insights resource you created for your application.

trans-unit.source: Choose Browse, Application Insights, your application
trans-unit.target: Choose Browse, Application Insights, your application

trans-unit.source: Create a continuous export.
trans-unit.target: Create a continuous export.

trans-unit.source: Choose Settings, Continuous Export, Add
trans-unit.target: Choose Settings, Continuous Export, Add

trans-unit.source: Let some data accumulate.
trans-unit.target: Let some data accumulate.

trans-unit.source: Sit back and let people use your application for a while.
trans-unit.target: Sit back and let people use your application for a while.

trans-unit.source: Telemetry will come in and you'll see statistical charts in [metric explorer](app-insights-metrics-explorer.md) and individual events in [diagnostic search](app-insights-diagnostic-search.md).
trans-unit.target: Telemetry will come in and you'll see statistical charts in [metric explorer](app-insights-metrics-explorer.md) and individual events in [diagnostic search](app-insights-diagnostic-search.md).

trans-unit.source: And also, the data will export to your storage.
trans-unit.target: And also, the data will export to your storage.

trans-unit.source: Inspect the exported data.
trans-unit.target: Inspect the exported data.

trans-unit.source: In Visual Studio, choose **View / Cloud Explorer**, and open Azure / Storage.
trans-unit.target: In Visual Studio, choose **View / Cloud Explorer**, and open Azure / Storage.

trans-unit.source: (If you don't have this menu option, you need to install the Azure SDK: Open the New Project dialog and open Visual C# / Cloud / Get Microsoft Azure SDK for .NET.)
trans-unit.target: (If you don't have this menu option, you need to install the Azure SDK: Open the New Project dialog and open Visual C# / Cloud / Get Microsoft Azure SDK for .NET.)

trans-unit.source: In Visual Studio, open Server Browser, Azure, Storage
trans-unit.target: In Visual Studio, open Server Browser, Azure, Storage

trans-unit.source: Make a note of the common part of the path name, which is derived from the application name and instrumentation key.
trans-unit.target: Make a note of the common part of the path name, which is derived from the application name and instrumentation key.

trans-unit.source: The events are written to blob files in JSON format.
trans-unit.target: The events are written to blob files in JSON format.

trans-unit.source: Each file may contain one or more events.
trans-unit.target: Each file may contain one or more events.

trans-unit.source: So we'd like to read the event data and filter out the fields we want.
trans-unit.target: So we'd like to read the event data and filter out the fields we want.

trans-unit.source: There are all kinds of things we could do with the data, but our plan today is to write some code to move the data to a SQL database.
trans-unit.target: There are all kinds of things we could do with the data, but our plan today is to write some code to move the data to a SQL database.
